race.comment: TOO MUCH TALK (3) was building nicely before landing the knockout blow at Belmont last start in a $100k race, jumping the $3.70 favourite. This looks to shape well from a handy barrier under Fiore and his recent form rates highly. Can make it back-to-back wins. COVERT ROSE (1) was slightly disappointing last start at this track and trip but was building nicely prior to that effort. Chris Parnham rides now from a sticky gate, though she has shown good early speed in the past. Ticks a few boxes and can play a leading role. WORCESTER (6) didn't fire as the favourite here 18 days ago when beaten 4L. He was in good touch prior to that however, so I'm willing to forgive one poor run. He's well placed to bounce back off the inside this time. HOBA WEST (5) never got into the race last start but rising to the mile now is a big tick. Can feature. HARBIN (4) can go on with the job following a good win here last time out.
